# Security Standards

## Core Principles

### 1. Zero Trust Architecture
- Never trust user input — validate everything
- Assume breach — design defense in depth
- Verify explicitly — authenticate and authorize every request
- Use least privilege — minimal permissions by default

### 2. Defense in Depth
- Multiple layers of security controls
- Fail securely — default to deny on errors
- Log security events — audit trails for incidents
- Encrypt data — in transit (TLS) and at rest

### 3. Security by Design
- Threat modeling during planning
- Security requirements in definition of done
- Secure defaults — opt-in for risky features

