## Secrets Management

### Environment Variables

```bash
# .env.local (gitignored)
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/db"
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-secret-key-min-32-chars"
NEXTAUTH_URL="https://yourdomain.com"
API_KEY="sk-..."
```

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Use process.env
const apiKey = process.env.API_KEY

// ❌ BAD: Hardcoded secrets
const apiKey = 'sk-1234567890'
```

### Secret Validation on Startup

```typescript
// lib/env.ts
import { z } from 'zod'

const envSchema = z.object({
  DATABASE_URL: z.string().url(),
  NEXTAUTH_SECRET: z.string().min(32),
  NEXTAUTH_URL: z.string().url(),
  API_KEY: z.string().startsWith('sk-')
})

export function validateEnv() {
  const result = envSchema.safeParse(process.env)
  if (!result.success) {
    console.error('❌ Missing required environment variables:', result.error.format())
    process.exit(1)
  }
  return result.data
}

validateEnv() // Call in next.config.js or custom server
```

### Secret Rotation

Support multiple secrets during rotation. Accept both old and new during transition, then remove old after grace period.

