## Security Checklist for PRs

### Mandatory Review Items

**Before merging any PR, verify:**

#### Input Validation
- [ ] All user inputs validated with Zod schemas
- [ ] Server-side validation implemented (not just client)
- [ ] File uploads have type and size restrictions
- [ ] SQL/NoSQL queries use parameterization

#### Authentication & Authorization
- [ ] Protected routes require authentication
- [ ] Permission checks on sensitive operations
- [ ] Resource ownership verified before modification
- [ ] Session management secure (HTTP-only cookies)

#### XSS Prevention
- [ ] No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without sanitization
- [ ] User content escaped by default
- [ ] CSP headers configured

#### CSRF Protection
- [ ] State-changing requests have CSRF tokens
- [ ] CORS configured correctly
- [ ] SameSite cookie attribute set

#### Security Headers
- [ ] HSTS enabled
- [ ] X-Frame-Options set
- [ ] X-Content-Type-Options set

#### Secrets Management
- [ ] No secrets in code (use environment variables)
- [ ] `.env` files in `.gitignore`

#### Error Handling
- [ ] Errors don't leak sensitive information
- [ ] Stack traces hidden in production
- [ ] Security events logged

#### Dependencies
- [ ] No known vulnerabilities (`npm audit`)
- [ ] Dependencies up to date

### `<SECURITY_REVIEW>` Tag Usage

**Use this tag when conducting security reviews:**

```markdown
<SECURITY_REVIEW>
**Threat Model:**
- Attack vector: SQL injection via search parameter
- Impact: Full database access
- Likelihood: High (public endpoint)

**Mitigation:**
1. Added Zod validation for search input
2. Switched to parameterized query
3. Added rate limiting (10 req/10s)

**Verification:**
- [x] Unit tests for invalid inputs
- [x] Integration test for SQL injection attempt
</SECURITY_REVIEW>
```

